Package math.shell.linearAlgebra.calculator

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    CalculatorParser
    Parses user input into commands for the calculator to perform
    Determinant
    Operations involving determinants, cofactors, minors, and adjoints
    Driver
    A linear algebra calculator that does singular matrix operations that can be chained in subsequent inputs
    ElementaryRowOperations
    A series of elementary row operations that are the basis of linear algebra
    ErrorMessages
    A list of Strings used for error messages and exceptions
    ExternalStorage
    Methods that deal with reading and writing the calculators external storage, stored in "calculator_storage.txt"
    GaussianElimination
    Reduce matrices to row echelon form and reduced row echelon form
    InterfaceMethods
    Methods that are strictly for the calculator interface
    InternalStorage
    A container that holds Matrices, mapping variable names to Matrices
    Inverse
    Finds the inverse of a matrix
    LastBigDecimalOutput
    A container with one slot that holds the last calculator output of type BIGDECIMAL
    LastEquationInput
    A container with one slot that holds the last equation the user inputs
    LastMatrixOutput
    A container with one slot that holds the last output of type MATRIX
    Matrix
    Constructs a Matrix object that can be used for linear algebra purposes.
    MatrixArithmetic
    A series of operations that involve Matrix arithmetic
    MatrixConstructorTests
    A series of tests on 2D arrays, used for finding attributes of matrices when making them
    MultiDimensionalArray
    Methods that involve operations on 2D arrays
    Print
    A series of methods that involve printing
    StringUtils
    Methods that involve taking information out of strings or editing strings
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    CalculatorParser.HitOrMiss
    As parser checks which operation to run, if runs an operation, status of parser becomes HIT, not running through any other operation checkers
    CalculatorParser.OutputType
    Last type outputted by the calculator, starts at NULL, and switches off between MATRIX and BIGDECIMAL
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    IncorrectSyntaxException
    This runtime exception is thrown in case where user inputs equation that parser cannot handle
    NoMatrixInQueueException
    This runtime exception is thrown in case where user tries to do operation that requires a matrix on last output, but last output not of type OutputType.MATRIX
    NonSquareMatrixException
    This exception is thrown in case where user tries to do operation that requires a square matrix on non-square matrix
    NothingInQueueException
    This runtime exception is thrown in case where user tries to do operation on last output, but no operations have been performed and nothing in calculator queue
    NotInvertibleException
    This runtime exception is thrown in case where user tries to invert a non-invertible matrix
    NotLeadingOneRowException
    This exception is thrown in case where user tries to do operation that requires a leading one row, on a non-leading one row
    UndefinedSolutionException
    This exception is thrown in case where matrix operation is undefined
    ZeroRowException
    This exception is thrown in case where operation requires a non-zero row
